title: Great  product
text: I have been using this product now for nearly 3 weeks and many candida overgrowth symptoms are very reduced, some eliminated.  The ONLY reason I did not give it 5 stars: THE DOSING DIRECTIONS ARE NOT GOOD!  A relative who is a doctor recommended this product, along with Pau D'Arco.  We failed to discuss dosage (won't make that mistake again!!!).  On Day 1, I took the recommended 5 capsules with breakfast, lunch and dinner.  By 11 pm I was violently ill - the sickest I have been for a long time, including stomach pain and tenderness.  I was fine by morning.  I called my relative - we decided to use 1 capsule 3x per day, slowly building to 3 capsules 3x per day.  So far so good!!  Generally I am not oversensitive to supplements.  I feel that the dosage recommendation on the bottle is rather irresponsible.  I have also cut out alcohol, sugar and am eating low carb, so "starve" the candida of what it loves.

I am a personal trainer and fitness instructor and I was looking for a multi-vitamin with the most bang for my health buck. It is hard these days to find a good multi-vitamin that has good ingredients and is really bioavaliable for your body to use. This product has a plethora of great things for your body including CoQ10 and many of your Colloidal Minerals which is a bonus from a lot of mult-vitamins. A few things that I wish were different are:
1. Vitamin D comes in several forms and in this multi-vitamin it is in the form D2. Ideally, especially in the winter you want vitamin D3 which is primarily given from the sun.. The other main downside I saw with this product is first it‚Äôs not organic and under other ingredients at the very bottom it says ‚Äúnatural flavors‚Äù which can be almost anything including high fructose corn syrup (HFCS). It also has potassium skrbate as a preservative, which is not great. Why not ascorbic acid or something. Overall, a great product though both for quality and price.

1. I have the A360 and the lame Polar wrist strap broke (that little white plastic thing fell out) and really started to stink and thus it was time to look for a replacement. Since the Polar strap is really lame and expensive, it was a no brainer NOT to get another one from Polar and thus I decided to take a risk on this third party strap. The following are some bottomline notes:
a: Size: one size and it does tend on the larger side of things. I a man, 5ft 8in, medium build and this strap fits snug, but I have to go near the end of the strap to do so... which leaves a lot of strap at the other end... which I cut off. I would think that for many women, this may be too big (of course depending on build).
b: Does this thing actually work? At first, I thought this was a dud because the inside "housing" didn't have the rigid component that the original Polar strap has. Furthermore, when I put my A360 insight, the thing popped out when I put the strap on and I was about to return it. Instructions? Don't even bother due to the low quality of instructions and basically everyone who is buying this already owns the A360/370 and thus knows how to put it in. However, all I have to say is, really look at the unit in the strap, ensure that it is completely embedded in the strap and it will definitely work / stay in place. I can't explain it any better; it definitely does work, the price is right, good colors; just work with the unit and you'll be happy with it.

I was given these to drink and they tasted exactly like a fruit punch drink, Kool-aid, etc. It helped me re-gain the weight that I needed to and during the last three months, it has allowed me to train for a half marathon without worry of my weight becoming unstable again.
Thank you to the makers of this product. I highly recommend it to anyone who needs an extra dose of protein and calories throughout their day and especially to anyone who may have trouble drinking Ensure or Boost products.

title: Nice product!
text:
Bought this when PURISURE was called Wholesale Health Connection. Printing on the bag I received indicates "100 % Satisfaction Guaranteed. If you are not completely satisfied with your WHC purchase, contact us for a full refund."

Purchased the product, quality was good, when bag was first opened. Within about 30 days, the product started smelling rancid. I presume the rancid smell was due to the bag's airtight ziplock seal quickly being made useless, by any product that passed by the seal. Even though the package shows an expiration date of 8-30-2020, I had used less than half the bag (in the winter of 2018,) before product became too rancid for safe / effective use.

The company has NOT bothered to respond to ANY of my attempts to reach them. Two voicemail messages, a week apart, were NOT responded to. Two emails I sent, (help@wholesalehealthconnection.com and returns@wholesalehealthconnection.com,) were NOT responded to. Based on the packaging graphics, same phone number, and same voicemail messaging, for Wholesale Health Connection and Purisure, Purisure is exactly the same company as Wholesale Health Connection.

If I were to order the product again, I would immediately transfer the contents to an airtight container, and toss in a silica gel pack, to help eliminate moisture. On the other hand, I see little reason to trust this company with another order, since my four efforts to contact them have accomplished nothing, aside from wasting my time AND money.

title: One Star
text:
I must say that when I first heard about this product I was extremely skeptical. I am a college student, and although I'm ashamed to admit it, I have used prescription ADD medications in the past to help me focus and give me the energy to complete large assignments. I began looking for an over the counter supplement that would give me similar concentration and energy, which led me to elebra. I have been taking these pills for a week now and I am very satisfied with the results.

I have been taking elebra for five days and have felt results every time. Although it is recommended that you take three capsules, I only take two. I took three once and felt sick (nausea and a headache, due to me being a small person with an extremely low tolerance to all substances). With two capsules, however, I feel an almost instantaneous boost of energy and concentration. I took two pills this morning, after hours of laying around my house staring at my to-do list with no drive to do anything on it, and within twenty minutes time I felt focused enough to attack my first task. Even when you're feeling lazy, elebra gives you the perfect boost of energy that you feel that you might as well do something productive with it! I've even taken these pills before a night out with friends to increase my energy and social engagement. Works like a charm.

Of course, the results are not as profound as prescription ADD medications, but if you're looking for something natural and over the counter to give you just enough energy to get through the day, this really works.

title: Great quality and easily absorbed.
text: After suffering through a sinus infection and bronchitis and being prescribed many antioniotics and a steroid treatment, after two months I was finally feeling better, still not great but better. Then I noticed my tongue felt like I had a hairball stuck on it. Yep it was covered in a white coating. Went to my clinic and my usual doctor wasn‚Äôt in that day so I saw another provider that put me on nystatin for 14 days after diagnosing it as thrush. Made perfect sense after all the antibiotics. 13 days later there was no improvement on my tongue. I went to the walk in clinic and the provider there said clearly I had Candida overgrowth and nothing but a Candida diet, a lot of probiotics and other supplements was going to help. So I began the miserable diet and ordered oregano oil, coconut oil, probiotics and a multi vitamin. I went online looking for anything that might help. I felt terrible most of the time and my tongue was so disgusting I was willing to try anything. I found info on this product on someone‚Äôs Candida blog. Well kinda pricey but I had to do something because the other stuff wasn‚Äôt working. So I continued with the diet, probiotics other supplements and added sf722 into my routine. I started feeling better, I felt like I was beginning to feel alive again. Still the nasty coated tongue though. After my months supply was used up I ordered again. Still feeling like I was improving, I was having more good days than bad. By now three months had gone by and I was following that diet, taking all the supplements, doing anything and everything I saw recommended for Candida overgrowth. But why was my tongue still gross? So I said well I gotta see my primary doctor again, this is just not right. He took one look in my mouth and said I dong think that‚Äôs Candida at all, it‚Äôs bacterial. I left ya office with an antibacterial prescription and instructions to return to a normal diet and just be me. I still had some sf722 left and since it was so expensive I decided to finish it off. I have been done with it for a couple weeks now. The antibacterial did it‚Äôs job on helping me feel better overall, although my tongue is still coated, which I‚Äôm told may take months to get rid of but at least after the culture, it‚Äôs peoven to be not Candida. And At least I feel human again. But I find myself considering ordering more of the sf722, because even though I never truly had a Candida problem, and this probably does help with that, I just feel that it made my guts and body feel better in general. However it could have been related to the diet I was following also. So I realize this may not be all that helpful if a review, if you have been diagnosed with Candida or even suspect you may have some issues with it, give this stuff a try. I totally recommend it, Candida or no Candida.

title: Calidad buen precio
text:
OK. So, I got this product yesterday and somehow forgot all the reviews about the terrible taste. So, what did I do? I recklessly put 1/4 tsp of the straight powder directly on my tongue and looked around for my water bottle. Oy vay!!! That was not an experience I would care to repeat again in the near future, far future, or any future! That was seriously the most putrid taste I have ever experienced in my life! I drank and drank water and more water. No dice. It wasn't letting up. So, I looked around for the strongest tasting stuff I could find in the fridge, which was sauerkraut. No go. It just made the sauerkraut taste horrible too. So, I drank more water and resigned myself to just letting it wear off. Took awhile.
Today, I read over all the reviews with the word "taste" in them. Realized that juice or lemonade or anything of the liquid sort was not going to cut it. So, I thought it over and came up with the following technique:
1. take 1/4 tsp (or however much your chosen serving might be) stir and dissolve in about 4 ozs of warm water. The less water, the better. It's just a carrier and you don't want to extend the experience...
2. Add 1-2 Tbsp of lemon juice. Stir again.
3. Take 1 heaping teaspoon of Peanut butter, and eat it, but leave a good coating on your tongue and all around your teeth and mouth.
4. Give your liquid a final stir and drink it all down without breathing (you might want to actually hold your nose while doing this, if you're not experienced at it).
5. Take a bit more peanut butter and eat it.
6. Now you can resume breathing again. You will not have tasted a thing, except the peanut butter.

The idea is that the peanut butter coats your gustatory glands (the glands you taste with). Holding your nose while eating or drinking anything actually blocks you from tasting most anything. You might get a bit of the lemon taste coming through, but nothing else. If you eat the second spoonful of peanut butter, it will clean out all other tastes that may have gotten through when drinking the liquid. I know this because I ventured taking a breath while I was drinking the Magnesium and I did encounter a slight taste of the foul stuff when doing so. Very slight. Maybe less than 10% of the original taste from yesterday. However, I stopped breathing, finished drinking, took the second helping of peanut butter and breathed again and encountered nothing but the taste of peanut butter at that point.

I will expect a statue to be erected in my honor by all my grateful followers... üòÑ

I cannot yet comment on the actual quality or effect of the product, hence the neutral 3 stars. I consider it a plus that I am still alive after yesterday's experience...

I decided that I would try it, but would remain as objective as possible so I could share with everyone else my thoughts on the matter. First off, let me say that I did not think there was anything wrong with pornography and/or masturbation. Count me in the camp of people who think (thought) it might even be healthy. After reading The OPAN Program manual, my thoughts have admittedly changed a bit. I have realized that perhaps these things may not be as benign as I had previously suspected.  Many of the patterns of behavior described in the book I have seen in my life. While the book isn't that long it gave me a new perspective. I almost found it enlightening and for that reason alone, I decided to put my heart into the program and started taking the Resetrol supplements. Here's what I can say after a couple weeks: 1) It is not as easy as I would have thought to stop doing something that previously I didn't think was a problem 2) The Resetrol supplements help. I know the book has explanations for why they work, but being the skeptic I am, I still don't get how they are working 3) I feel good. Not that I felt that bad before, but I guess I was just used to the constant dysphoria. This has been a pleasant change. I'm still on the fence sometimes about this whole thing, but when I see the difference this has made in my life in just a few months I can't help but wonder if there is something to it.

title: Everything went smooth love the products will purchase again
text:
Update 7/16/17: Thank you so very much to all readers who inputted to me on a solution for the non-supported Apple App issue. There are work-arounds for settings on Apple devices to allow the app/software to be "trusted", (and function when opened) and as one excellent response noted, there ARE other apps on Apple's Appstore web-site that are registered and approved by Apple, that will work w/ this model/make watch.

I guess my gripe is with the manufacturer (and/or seller) in that why don't they simply offer an app that is Apple verified and supported like so many other fitness trackers out there are? I've come across several very similar watches on Amazon that have full support through Apple for that model's app. Install the app through the Apple App store and no issues arise in dealing wth using a "3rd party app" to use as a work-around for the problem.

-----------------------------------
So sorry to find out upon receiving that this company (China) and its app is not sanctioned, supported nor registered with Apple nor its Apps. It installs outside of any Apple source (App Store or iTunes) and the security feature in IOS prevented this app from running after installing it in what the company does for a work-around to be able to get it installed at all (and not from any Apple website).

I got flags for unknown developer, and a security warning (is any data shared?).

Returned this to Amazon and ordered one of many other "Fitbit Clones" that do have supported software in Apples App Store. text:
We've had this scale for about 2 weeks, and so far so good! I purchased this scale because birthing websites recommend weighing yourself and then weighing yourself with your baby to check your baby's weight, so wanted to make sure I got a really accurate scale (or at least one that gives me the same reading in at least two consecutive weighs). I always read all the 1-star reviews for a product before deciding whether to buy, and if the problems noted in the 1-star reviews are serious enough or consistent enough, I choose not to purchase the product, even if it has 4.5 stars out of 100+ reviews. I was on the fence about this scale based on the other 1-star reviews, but am glad they proved not to pertain to the scale we received.

The product arrived two days earlier than expected, came with the necessary batteries, and worked perfectly upon first use. My husband, brother, and I all weighed ourselves twice to make sure we got the same weight measurement each time, and we did! For some reason it takes a while to secure my husband's weight each time he steps on the scale - it always fluctuates 0.2 - 0.4 lbs in difference and we don't know why - so he stands on the scale for up to 15 seconds sometimes before he gets a settled reading, but for my brother and myself it takes fewer than 5 seconds each time. This hasn't changed since we got the item, and since my husband doesn't care too much about his exact weight (0.2 - 0.4 lbs deviation is not that big a deal to him), we like the scale just fine. The bright blue LED screen is quite bright, though, and stays on for about 30 seconds after use, so I just wouldn't weigh myself in the middle of the night after using the restroom, since it would definitely jar me awake. The scale is very lightweight and thin, making it easy to transfer between different bathrooms/hard floors.

Would definitely recommend!

title: We like it
text:
This is a great scale for the price. I use it a few times a week to monitor weight loss / gain. I have confidence knowing that it is consistent and dependable.

The weight takes about 5 seconds to register - the numbers fluctuates within 1 pound when stepping on, and you must remain still until the number on the display starts blinking. At that point you can step off of the scale and the number remains on the display for about 20 seconds. Stepping back onto the scale after the display turns black then results in the same reading almost every time. Also, no need to tap a foot onto the scale to wake it up. Just stand on it and remain motionless and wait for the reading.

Another thing I like about this scale is the width and length - I'm 6'2" with size 12 feet that are wide. I don't have an issue with foot space, width of the scale, or covering the display when standing on it. I've never once felt like I was swaying / going to tip over, and I've never had an issue with accidentally stepping to close to a corner / side of the scale and had it tip over - meaning the rubber feet underneath are nice and close to the corners making for good stability.

I use this on a hard tile floor so I can't speak for use on carpet or softer materials. Also it doesn't have bluetooth or wifi connectivity - those things didn't matter to me, I was looking for size, a nice display, and consistency. If these are qualities you are looking for (as well as a good price point), this scale is a great choice.

text:
I like the idea of taking a multivitamin in one pill. I was currently taking handfuls of quality vitamins that I carefully selected. That being said, how do you review the benefits of a vitamin if there are no noticeable changes in your health? I replaced this with my usual routine and feel like it is a good quality product. I have noticed before that if I skip my vitamins, I am tired. This didn't happen when I switched to this. I did get a headache one day (associated with another product I was trying) and wondered if it was because I was not taking the magnesium supplement that I normally take. I checked the bottle to see if this contained magnesium, and it did say it contained 100%. Nevertheless, I took my magnesium supplement in addition and did gain some relief from the headache. This seems to be a quality product in one pill. As for the size of the pill, I have no problem with it, but I am used to taking handfuls of pills (supplements/vitamins) all at once. However, for someone who has a hard time, it's definitely not tiny. I would say it's about the size one would imagine for all of the daily vitamins packed into this one pill.

text:
I love this cream! I mostly use this as a night time moisturizer and I can truly stand behind this product because I am on my second jar. I figure this gives me solid support in stating my results since I have figured out most of the nuances of this cream. So here goes...

The texture of the cream is really comparable to a cold cream but is a little thinner. I honestly thought I could never use this because I have acne prone skin but gave it a try because someone recommended this to me. That being said, it has not made my acne worse or better. Instead, it just has really balanced out the ph of my face so now I'm not worried about half my face being dry and the other half oily. The tone of my skin is more even and I have no dry patches.

As for anti-wrinkle properties, I can't say it has made a difference in regards to this but then again I really don't use it for this purpose.

Overall, this is a great bargain and I would recommend this to anyone looking for a good night time moisturizer as this can get a little heavy for the morning. Plus, you really have to let the product sink into your skin and that can take some time. If you don't have that much time in the morning before work this will be a problem for applying makeup as I found out.

The jar is pretty big and the amount you are given is generous when compared to other brands. My first jar lasted me for a good 5 months!

title: nice scale for the money
text:
Just a really quick review to share my (unique?) experience:

Taste: No problem, especially considering you're drinking vitamins! I honestly expected the taste to be worse than it is. You just shoot it down - Don't let it touch the sides of your mouth, the insides of your cheeks, et cetera and it's fine. It doesn't even taste that bad using this method.

Results: Excellent! During the 1st two+ weeks: I saw substantial and very noticeable improvement overall. I felt great! Energy level was up I was happy as could be with this product. I could hardly believe how lucky I was to find it!

Then the bad news: Somewhere around the 3rd week Of taking these vitamins, I developed this unexplainable kidney pain.
Just both my kidneys hurt all the time , to the point where I was practically hunched over. It was not fun (and a little scary to be honest). Now I drink nothing but bottled water all day long ‚Äî lots of it. Been drinking lots of bottled water for years now...
I figured that the only thing it could be from was the vitamins ‚Äî so I stopped taking them right away....
In less than a week the kidney pains subsided, until they were completely gone.
But my energy, and general feeling of well being that I got in the 1st two weeks is also gone. üò¢
1st 2 Weeks: I feel amazing!
3rd Week: I feel like I'm going to croak from kidney failure.
As crazy as it sounds, I'm thinking about giving it another shot... Hopefully, I'll be able to report on here as to exactly what happens?
If the kidney pain starts again I'll just stop it - For good this time.

title: Everything I expected
text:
Whoa .. where do I begin here? Okay lets start off with how amazing the taste is! I don't even know what to compare it too because it doesn't taste like yogurt to me as this is a bit more sticky & thick. Also, there is not a dairy flavor either so that is why I cannot compare it to yogurt. I am so glad I listened to the sales rep at my local Vitamin Shoppe. I thought he was just trying to get me to spend more money ;) This stuff goes for $19.99 in the V.S. right now and amazon is practically giving it away at a much ressonable price. Subscibe & safe, that's all I'll say about that.

How do I use? This stuff not only provides my body with important nutrients but because the flavor is so amazing, my smoothies just don't taste the same without it!
Here is my recipe for the ultimate smoothie.

1 cup of spinach ( don't be a sissy! you can't even taste it ;)
1/2 cup of cabbage
1 cup of frozen or fresh broccoli
a dash of vanilla extract
a dash of cinnamon
1 cup of almond milk

@ this point you are going to mix everything up in a blender and your smoothie will be green :)

Next add the following ingredients ..

1 whole banana
1/4 cup blackberries
1 cup strawberries
2 tbsp of Barlean's Organic Swirl Flax Oil/Strawberry flavor
1/2 cup of almond milk (if you need more then add more!)

Blend again for another minute or so and enjoy! I drink this bad boy before I exercise because it's LOADED with everything your body needs to get through a tuff workout. You can drink this after as well but I usually find it hard because I don't carry a blender with me ;)

Also I can't stress enough about using organic products, almost everything I buy is organic and frozen, or if it ain't frozen .. I cut it up and freeze it in little ziplock baggies (like the bananas). This week I had some left over cherry tomatos and I threw four of those into my shake. You guys! I could not even taste them :)

All you taste is the fruit and like I mentioned before .. that wonderful taste of the Swirl Flax Oil. Yum! I'm off to make myself a shake now :)

title: Good product
text:
Pros: Cheap, reasonably accurate, easy to use and read.
Cons: Cheap, low quality control.
I liked this scale because it came in grey; a nice contrasting color less likely to show prints. Plus, it was pretty much the same as higher priced models. Well, the low price comes with it's drawbacks. It failed within 36 hours. I asked for a replacement and it was hassle free. Mind you that doesn't include the hassle of dropping off the dead unit at the UPS store. The new one arrived reasonably quickly and has been functioning for the last three days. So, maybe it will last; but I'm keeping the packaging until the 30 day return period expires just in case. I recommend you do the same. That said, the light on the digital readout is a bit askew compared to the previous unit and doesn't equally light up the display. While a bit annoying, it's not enough reason to return it. However, it does indicate rather sloppy assembly and low quality control. Like I said, you get what you pay for. If you don't mind the possibility of spending time returning one of these for a replacement; it's a reasonable scale at a good price.

title: Easy to use.
text:
The suggested dose is 100mcg but this has worked well for me.
I swing shift every week night to day and this makes all the
difference. I'm a person who wakes up after 4 hours, so I'll
often take another if needed. Else I'll just lay there for 2
hours not sleeping. It just takes the edge off your thoughts
and lets's me push them back into sleep mode. Absolutely no
side effects. Larger doses made for vivid dreams.

Update: I have switched to liquid form when I ran out of
these. The liquid directions are 4 eye droppers for 1 mg.
So I use about 1/2 dropper of liquid or 125 micrograms.
It works well and very fast. Like about 5 minutes my eyes
start to droop. The very dramatic effect fades after a week
but who cares? At this low a dose you can take another dose
4 times a night if needed.

My only complaint would be the horrible taste. I'm not a fan of Stevia, or the berry flavor, which makes it hard to add it to just any smoothie, so I suggest that you dissolve a scoop in a little bit of water, and just take it as a shot! It gets the unappetizing flavor over with quickly, and personally, I find it fun to take an alcohol free shot! It makes me feel like old times, but with no hangover in the morning!

I could only give four stars because of the taste, and the price. This product is definitely worth the money, but it is really expensive.

I was given these to drink and they tasted exactly like a fruit punch drink, Kool-aid, etc. It helped me re-gain the weight that I needed to and during the last three months, it has allowed me to train for a half marathon without worry of my weight becoming unstable again.
Thank you to the makers of this product. I highly recommend it to anyone who needs an extra dose of protein and calories throughout their day and especially to anyone who may have trouble drinking Ensure or Boost products.

title: Five Stars
text:
I had Candida a few years back and my nutritionist recommended undecenoic acid. At the time all I had heard of, for natural remedies, was a severe sugar restricted diet (still the same BTW) and caprilic acid. Some say oregano, garlic, black walnut, pau d'arco and other natural herbs help also by I have only tried garlic, which is good but I can't tell much effect. I started on the Thorne Research SF 722 and it worked within about 4 weeks, although I think I stayed on it for 6 to 8 as recommended by my nutritionist at the time. I had a recent recurrence and immediately used my leftover supply but was (my bad) not as strict about diet. As soon as I ran out of the SF 722, the Candida hit with a vengeance. I immediately ordered this on Amazon and reinitiated the stricter diet (see below). In between I tried to use caprilic acid, which works, but not as well. I started back on this and, while I can tell I am not ok yet, I can definitely tell it works. I use 6 to 8 gel caps per day. I think the bottle recommends more but, as I recall, 4 x twice a day was what my nutritionist had recommended (actually, I thought he said only once per day but it's been long enough I can't remember). It's only been less than 1 week since the 're-start so I'm still on it.

Diet: no matter what, you have to be extremely careful. NO extra SUGAR , none, nada. No sugar added to food, none, nada, nope. Look at all labels. At the very least, 1 month. Sorry folks, that's how to fight this. My nutritionist recommended APPLES (the undecenoic acid can stop up the gut). Just don't overdo on Apple's. Another reviewer said granny Smith, yes, that reviewer is probably right but I remember using any Apple, I just only did about half a day and it worked then and seems to work now. For the same reason, DRINK LOTS OF WATER. 64 ounces a day is often recommended. If you don't, you are going to have a lot of gut problems worse than the Candida. My nutritionist recommended no fruit except Apple's and berries. I am very careful not to overdo berries but they are often lower in sugar than some fruit. Many people say to avoid ALL fruit. I'd just say at first, avoid all except green apples, lemons and limes for a couple of weeks, then add berries in small quantities. No other fruit for 2-3 months. No sugar for longer if you can or at least 2 months. No cheese or fermented products, no mushrooms, very, very low quantities of carrots and white potatoes for at least a month. Personally I restrict almost all high starch/high glycemic carbohydrates (turn straight to sugar in the body). BUY A GOOD ENZYME AND PROBIOTIC AND EAT YOGURT. The gut needs these seriously to repair any damage done. Read up on this. Take them hours apart from taking the FS 722.

4 diet comments: sugar in foods, sweet potatoes, grains and Stevia. (1) sugars in foods: read all labels carefully. Soup and lunch meats/sausage are two weird foods that often have more sugar than you might expect. (2) sweet potatoes: are lower glycemically than you might expect. My nutritionist recommended them and they work well for my body. If you eat them and you do not get better, eliminate, this might be a personal thing. I do NOT agree with the reviewer who said to avoid them. (3)grains, I personally am probably gluten intolerant and eating gluten may have been part of the problem. Avoid most grains, especially wheat and corn. However, my body seems to tolerate rice and many gluten-free grains, especially the "seed" grains and those with higher protein (e.g. quinoa, amaranth and buckwheat) but the reviewer that cautioned against all grains may be right. I personally still eat grains but NO YEAST, NO RAISED BREAD. I eat rice crackers, rice chips (no corn added, Lundberg makes one), and my own pancakes I make with Stevia. (4) stevia: I do not agree with the reviewer on this one. Even my nutritionist recommended it. But it CAN increase your "craving" for sugar. With me personally, I quelled it.

title: Bad product
text:
Literally crap. We have been using this thermometer we bought for like $3 at a grocery store for YEARS. Very unreliable, so I figured it's time to get serious and purchase a real thermometer. All the positive reviews persuaded me to give this product a try. Ugh, so disappointed.

We followed the instructions to a T (wife is a big reader on instructions, and she's the one that opened it up). Yet, our temperatures are never consistent. I know that our temperature is likely to vary from time to time, but what we got each time was just ridiculous. The majority of the time, I was only 93 degrees. What the heck. I really don't think that's true. We would measure about 4-5 times in a row, in the same spot, just to see if maybe it was like a false reading. Nope. All 5 measurements would be completely different. I would be 93.4, 97.7, 95.4, 98.3, and 96.5. What kind of thermometer is this? Even the cheap one we got from the grocery store was at least always consistent in the readings - like if I was 97.6, then I would be 97.6 when I measured again back-to-back.

I was sick with a terrible cold for a week, and I felt like I had a fever during some of the days. Obviously no temperature confirmation, thanks to this crappy thermometer. According to the thermometer, I was only 93 degrees despite the feverish forehead and chills. Right.

Literal piece of trash. I'm hoping we can return this because it's completely useless. Oh and I want to point out we use this orally.

text:
OK. I have been asked to review this product from Zahler. This is the 2nd time I've ordered it. The first time it came in a bottle with a dropper that was a little faulty but seemed to work well enough (the dropper stick repeatedly came out of the rubber top and had to be reinserted before use). My toddlers drank up their juice with vitamin D drops daily without a problem. But then they got old enough to move a chair over to the counter where the bottle was stored. Needless to say, it only takes about 90 seconds of unsupervised toddler time for 2 two year olds to snag a dropper bottle and bite the top off.
The second time I ordered the product, there was a new dispensing mechanism that did away with the dropper. However, it is not as precise as the dropper once was. Now, I have to give the bottle a quick shake to make a drop (only one??) come out into the glass. While it is more child-proof, it is less precise. I don't think it matters as much with vitamin D as it would with other supplements but it is technically a flaw.
I'm somewhat satisfied with the product packaging. Regarding the actual vitamin D, all I can say is that my kids haven't developed rickets. So I guess it's doing its job.

title: Accurate read every time!
text:
For people looking for Phytoplankton, this is a good product...But, and this is a big but -- my experience is that it really does not have any effect on your body whatsoever. What DOES have an effect on your body is the WATER that you drink with it.

I tried an experiment. For one week, I took 4 to 6 drops of the phytoplankton with 12 oz of water early in the morning as soon as I woke up - I felt good every morning that week with my mood generally improved. I thought I had really discovered something.

I stopped taking it for a week to see if the effect was real. That week, my mood was not as good overall. I was generally more irritable and a bit thirsty throughout the day.

I thought maybe the water had just as much of an effect as the Phytoplankton. To find out whether this was the case, the third week, I took only 12 oz of water with no phytoplankton in it. I felt exactly like I did the first week. My mood was generally improved. I felt better. And I was more productive at work.

My conclusion is that drinking 12 oz of water immediately after waking up makes me feel better, and that the Phytoplankton is just a placebo. It's possible that this stuff has some real effects for people, but I'm skeptical - I think it is all hype. The real effect is because of the water you take with it.

Don't believe me?...try it for yourself. It won't cost you anything. Water is free (usually).

text:
This is a good basic thermometer. It reads very slightly low when used under the tongue or under the arm, but that's really to be expected of any thermometer. The most accurate reading of your internal temperature is to actually measure inside your body, which is rectal. I did two rectal readings within a couple of minutes and got 98.9F and then 98.7F.

I love that the tip is soft and flexible. I don't have to worry about hurting my newborn if she moves suddenly while I'm getting her temperature. It took about 10 seconds to get each reading.

The only negative thing I have to say about it is all the beeps once it gives the reading. No one needs 10 beeps to notify them that the result is ready. It's really annoying to hear, but turning it off as soon as you see the result is the solution I came up with.

This stuff is plain nasty tasting. I bought it to help with my sleep and have yet to see a major difference. I don't know how much longer I will be able to tolerate the horrible fish taste, even mixed with yogurt. My Fitbit says my deep sleep is longer, but I don't put a lot of stock in the information in the first place. I don't feel any more rested than before I started taking it. About the only answer I see to help with the taste is to buy a capsule filling machine.

I have to wonder why various reviewers have totally different takes on the taste - from no taste to baking soda taste to fish sauce taste. It makes one wonder if the batches are different, and if so, why? I have bought other supplements from this company and felt they were of excellent quality. Seeing different answers to the country of origin, supposedly all from the manufacturer, make me question what is going on with this product. It may wind up in my garbage soon!

Update: The manufacturer contacted me about the one star review I left for their product. They immediately refunded my purchase price and shipped me a new scale. The new scale was easier to set up and pair with my phone. It is currently working. I have raised my review to 3 stars. After 45 days if the scale is still working as expected then I will again edit my review and raise to 5 stars based on the excellent customer service I received.

The scale has now been working for 45 days and I am both pleased with the product and the customer service I received.

I felt the effects of this product the same day that I started taking it. Mainly, my stomach doesn't feel uneasy for most of the day like it used to. Based on my symptoms, I'm fairly certain I have Candida-related health issues, and after feeling the immediate improvement from this product, I have stronger evidence to confirm my suspicion.

Other benefits of this product are that my skin feels better. It seems more elastic and moisturized. This is an awesome, unexpected benefit, considering I was having psoriasis-like patches on my eyebrows, elbows, and knees probably due to leaky gut (not fun). I took this product last year along with a cleansing/experimental diet consisting mainly of greens and veggies, and I remember feeling better than ever. I've isolated the foods that affect me to dairy(not cheese so much as liquid milk), sugar, and gluten. Again, these are the foods that would negatively affect a person with candidiasis. My current experiment is to see how much this product works while maintaining a "regular" diet. Granted, I'm eating a lot less of these types of foods, but I have to say that this product allows me to eat this stuff in moderation and not feel like crap. Probably the single-most helpful supplement I've taken, right up there with Saccharomyces Boulardii.

text: I am in my 30's and have had ME/CFS since my teens.  I have a lot of GI issues and this product helped a lot with bloating. I've never thought that a strict Candida diet was particularly sustainable or worth it, but to each their own!  I pair this with a strong probiotic.  It's hard to know which reviews to trust, and I personally am always dubious of reviews that claim a product was entirely life-changing, but I will say that I was impressed how quickly this product started to take effect and how the effects have endured.  I definitely recommend it if you have Candida issues.

title: I like that you don't have to wait for it to ...
text:
Below you can read my original 1-star review, which I labeled "Inaccurate and Inconsistent".

I have modified this to 3 stars. If used correctly the thermometer can give both accurate and repeatable oral measurements. The secret is understanding what the term "fast" means in the description. It means the time to a fever/no fever determination, NOT the time to an accurate temperature. That is why there are so many reviews complaining about obviously low and inconsistent readings. When the thermometer beeps in 15 seconds or so it does not have an accurate temperature displayed, just whatever measurement was there when it made its fever/ no fever determination.

So, to get this to work do the following:
1. Put the thermometer in the mouth for 1 minute. Take it out.
2. Ignore whatever it says. The purpose of (1) was to warm the device up.
3. Wait a minute with the mouth closed. The purpose of this is to let the mouth recover from (1).
4. Put the thermometer in the mouth again for a minimum of 60 seconds. Take it out.
5. Take the temperature reading.

I found the above gave accurate and repeatable measurements compared to both my known reference thermometers and a temporal artery thermometer.

I also want to complement the company's customer service department in their communications with me in response to my first review, as they worked to deal with my comments. They did offer to refund my money (which I am not doing). I would suggest, however, that the marketing materials be modified to be more accurate.

**************************************************
Original review:

I already have two thermometers that have proven accurate (but slow) over the years and was looking for something with a quicker readout. This unit does read out quickly--the sooner to get your wildly inaccurate, inconsistent readings. In general, way too low (oral). If I didn't already have something of known accuracy to compare to I'd be afraid I was sick!

It leaves my skin feeling really soft and healthy looking. The effects seem to last for quite a while and the longer you use it the better the results, I have found.

I first came across this cream when looking for something to cure my dad's eczema on his hands. The tips of his fingers had long deep splits in them and were incredibly painful for him. I happened across someone who advised using this propolis cream in conjunction with the Forever Living Aloe Vera juice [[ASIN:B00137JS3O Forever Aloe Vera Gel, 33.8 oz]]. You drink an 'egg cup' (about 2 tablespoons) twice a day and rub on the propolis cream. This cleared up my dad's eczema within a few days. Way more effective than the doctor's steroid creams. Later on, when his eczema came back, we tried just the cream on its own. It did work - but not as quickly or as effectively as doing the drink and the cream together. In the past we have also tried other brands of aloe vera cream and drinks - but they have not been as effective - so on this product I am brand loyal. After a couple of rounds of this, my dad's eczema disappeared completely and has never returned. Many years later, he experienced very dry skin on the palms of his hands as a side effect to taking some medication. The skin was literally peeling off in big sections. Once again, the doctor prescribed steroid cream that had no effect. He went back to the propolis cream and aloe vera drink and again within a few days his condition cleared up.

I would definitely recommend this cream generally and in combination with the Forever Living aloe vera drink for anyone with eczema or other skin conditions.

This was recommended to me by a dietician late last year. It's a bit spendy, but much better than buying the fish-oil pills and putting up with fishy burps all day.

I like to put my teaspoon's worth in my morning oatmeal, but it tastes good by itself. It may actually taste too good‚Äîit's tempting to have an extra spoonful or two, with the result being that a bottle doesn't last as long as it should. But again, it's better than putting up with that fishy taste from fish-oil pills.

I recommend not purchasing online, however. My order from Amazon arrived in one of those plastic envelopes with the bubble-wrap lining; this offered next to no protection of the contents. When I opened the package, the cap was cracked, and the seal had been punctured. Fortunately, Whole Foods is just a block away, so I was able to return it with no problem. Now I will only purchase new bottles from the store (whether Whole Foods or other local stores).

title: Five Stars
text:
Just a really quick review to share my (unique?) experience:

Taste: No problem, especially considering you're drinking vitamins! I honestly expected the taste to be worse than it is. You just shoot it down - Don't let it touch the sides of your mouth, the insides of your cheeks, et cetera and it's fine. It doesn't even taste that bad using this method.

Results: Excellent! During the 1st two+ weeks: I saw substantial and very noticeable improvement overall. I felt great! Energy level was up I was happy as could be with this product. I could hardly believe how lucky I was to find it!

Then the bad news: Somewhere around the 3rd week Of taking these vitamins, I developed this unexplainable kidney pain.
Just both my kidneys hurt all the time , to the point where I was practically hunched over. It was not fun (and a little scary to be honest). Now I drink nothing but bottled water all day long ‚Äî lots of it. Been drinking lots of bottled water for years now...
I figured that the only thing it could be from was the vitamins ‚Äî so I stopped taking them right away....
In less than a week the kidney pains subsided, until they were completely gone.
But my energy, and general feeling of well being that I got in the 1st two weeks is also gone. üò¢
1st 2 Weeks: I feel amazing!
3rd Week: I feel like I'm going to croak from kidney failure.
As crazy as it sounds, I'm thinking about giving it another shot... Hopefully, I'll be able to report on here as to exactly what happens?
If the kidney pain starts again I'll just stop it - For good this time.

text:
Super lightweight, barely know it's there. My last one felt like it was 5x heavier. The tracker also sits well on the wrist.

I love the secure strap with the secure loop which has a nib that clicks into one of the watch holes. I am pretty sure I lost my last tracker because it didn't have this feature and the strap got caught on something and fell off.

The sleep tracking isn't great but it is nice to have even if it's pretty inaccurate. Would be great if, within the veryFitPro app to confirm the sleep range like in my Samsung Health. Additionally I think it's less accurate than my Samsung Health. It's a little disappointing to see over 15% less steps on the tracker when i wear it 24/7 vs my Samsung Health phone app which is on a device I am not carrying on me 24/7. However changing it to my dominant arm did bring the tracked steps around 5% more than my cell phone.

The tracker doesn't start counting if less than 10 steps is detected. It also will deducting steps/zeroes out steps if it thinks you moved less than 30 steps. I have also noticed sometimes the steps don't increase even when walking like the pedometer has frozen.

I don't plan to use it for an alarm or for calls. I haven't checked out the SNS alerts, Frankly because most times I have my phone within reach if I am stationary.

The touch screen is pretty good. There's a little oval on a side of the tracker which will turn the screen on if it's out and flip through the stats.

Instructions could also be a bit better in the app...

text:
My wife and I love these! For the price, you are getting a complete multivitamin regiment for less than a dollar-a-day.
We are very active people doing kayaking and bicycling in the summer, and snowboarding/skiing, hiking in the winter. We are also year-round runners and do challenging yoga almost every day (you gotta relax on the weekend c'mon). We have both noticed a difference in taking these vitamin packs in our skin and nails, as well as our recovery time from exercise, and just a better overall healthy feeling. You can call that a placebo effect if you want, but the science in these is also something I like to research before I buy vitamins. They are all suspended in sunflower oil in capsules - which not only is a better delivery system for the vitamins to be absorbed by your body (take it from me I'm a NURSE), but sunflower oil is also more completely broken down by your body - I remember that from my biochem class, look it up you will see the full explanation!

Anyway - they are great vitamins, take the place of a whole bunch of individual pills you could take, and I have never gotten a broken pack. If you read some of the negative reviews they are only negative because the item arrived damaged - not that the vitamins were a bad product (so not really a reason to leave a bad review for the product, more like the seller or shipping fault)
I hope VPX keeps making these and does not focus solely on BANG energy drink - they make a lot of other good products with solid science behind them.

For individuals relying on accurate measurements to determine whether they are running a fever, this is a potentially dangerous assessment tool. ALSO, this thermometer is not returnable through Amazon.

title: High quality powder supplement packaged well
text:
I've run the gamut of energy and focus supplements, but few have had such consistent effects as Elebra. The clean, straight-forward packaging on the outside is a direct reflection of what's on the inside: a nice clean focus-enhancement supplement. I found my best dose at 2 capsules with no caffeine, but found that if I needed the extra boost, I could take three (the recommended dose) with or without caffeine, both to great effect. The additions of rhodiola and various vitamin b supplements, I think, is what really makes this blend special.

Often times, after a have a dose or two of a certain focus supplement, I feel the effects start to lessen, until there's really none at all. I took Elebra every two-three days for about three weeks (again, at various doses) and always felt the intended boost (which, of course, varied by the dose, when I took it in the day, how tired I was when I took it, etc). It's really increased my productivity, and I was able to get several looming projects completed that had been hanging over my head for weeks (take that, disorganized closet!).

Not all supplements are for every one, but this one is definitely worth giving a shot.

This is (by far) the best thing I've found to control my severe systemic candida. I ran out for a few days & was trying something else, & my candida returned immediately. I tried using this a year ago (2 caps 3 x per day) & quit, thinking that it didn't work. I have suffered with this condition for over 30 years, MD's were totally useless, they gave me multiple antibiotics (which worked VERY temporarily (maybe a couple of weeks), pain killers, sleeping pills, anti-inflamatories, & muscle relaxants (which masked the symptoms while on the drugs only). It wasn't until I saw a naturopath & was diagnosed immediately with candida, was I able to finally start getting it under control.
I actually cured myself once (in a week!) with plain garlic (3 - 4 cloves throughout the day - cut up & swallowed like little pills) I just took a clove every time I noticed any itching. Unfortunately, I went nuts eating sugar right away & just took a clove of garlic to stop any symptoms starting to come back. After going through a very stressful month along with my old (sugar) diet, my candida came back with a vengeance! It's now resistant to garlic & I've been diagnosed with a sensitivity to it as well! I was desperate to find something that would work as the candida was spiraling out of control. I browsed Amazon looking for something that was highly rated & came across people raving about SF722. I still had some, so I decided to try it again, & this time I took the full dose, (5 caps 3 x per day) & it worked! I've since added genestra black walnut on the advice of my ND & it is definitely keeping the candida at bay. I'm now looking to find a good detox for heavy metals as I've been diagnosed with a toxic load of, probably due to many amalgam fillings (which I've since had removed).

2/23/2015 Update! I got rid of the candida again, this time with asparagus! I ate some every day, either in my smoothie (3 - 4 stalks) or fried some up in a little butter with some pink salt (YUM!). I was able to go off of all the supplements, except I always take good probiotics!

text:
I was looking for a magnesium supplement that was easily absorbed but without the laxative effects that other forms can cause. I've tried magnesium citrate in the past and while it doesn't bother me, other family members have had a different experience.

Magnesium glycinate is supposed to be much less likely to cause digestive issues than citrate. BulkSupplements had a good price on the bulk powder so I thought I'd order some and see for myself. The good news is that we've have no issues at all with it.

If you plan to put the powder into gel caps, note that it isn't very dense which makes it harder to pack. In fact, after making a month's worth of caps, I've decided that the raw powder doesn't taste too bad after all.

This product is definitely worth a try if you need a good magnesium supplement without the laxative effects of magnesium citrate.

text:
Without the app - the scale works very well. Pop the included 4x AAA batteries into the back of the unit and stand on it. You'll only get the weight reading this way though

With the app - it still works well but may need to step on/off the scale to get it to record sometimes. Keep in mind you're downloading the EUFY Life app which is a dashboard for other EUFY products and the scale data is housed within this app (my gf had to get a copy of the app on her own phone to track her own set of data - not a problem for me but as another reviewer mentioned it was a point of contention for them). The Bluetooth synching is quick, but as mentioned above sometimes you step onto the scale and the app will think and think but nothing will happen. Just stepping off and on should does the trick, slight inconvenience and not consistent. I'm not a huge health nut or anything like that so the information provided is clean and simple and provides some simple insights against what I believe is probably national averages. The history chart is also a nice touch. Everything in this package is simple and suits my casual needs

On a side note - I can't speak to the health "accuracy" but I did find that the first measurement seemed to be a bit high, after re-measuring each day over the weekend the numbers seem to have stabilized. I've only had it for a few days but will be sure to post an update after extended use as I do have some fitness goals to try to achieve :)

text: I‚Äôve been a mom for almost 36 years. In that time, I‚Äôve owned and used A LOT of thermometers.  This is one of the best I‚Äôve ever used. Want to know why? For one thing, the tip at the end is flexible. When using it on myself, I found this to be WONDERFUL! I have a VERY SERIOUS gag reflex. Most thermometers make me gag because when they‚Äôre up under my tongue they just always seem to push that special button that makes me‚Ä¶uck. BUT, with this one, I was able to bend it just a little‚Äîkeeping it up under my tongue‚Äîbut it pushed down instead of back and‚Ä¶tada!...no gagging. LOVE THAT. Another thing that just amazed me was how accurate it seemed to be. The first day I got it, I took my temperature 10 times throughout the day. Mind you, I was not sick. Just testing it out. It read between 98.3 and 98.8 all day; pretty steady. THEN, a few days later, my husband got sick. He had a high temp. We took a reading at 11:00 pm that read 102.3. The next day we took him to the doctor. HER thermometer read 102.1. If it‚Äôs reading the same as the doctor‚Äôs, I would take that to mean it‚Äôs accurate. One last thing and then I‚Äôll stop gushing. I LOVE the little happy/not happy faces on the read out. CUTE. But, practical too. My grandson is 8. He looked at the thermometer after taking a daytime temp for my husband and said, ‚ÄúGrammy, there‚Äôs a sad face. That means Papaw is really sick!‚Äù LOVE IT!

text:
This Somaluxe stretch mark treatment cream comes in a bottle with a safety sealed top. The cream is white and appears to be whipped. There is a definite scent to the cream which is a lot like unscented cocoa butter. There is a long list of organic oils and vitamins that have gone into this formula that are very impressive.

I bought this for stretch marks that have appeared on legs and arms due to weight loss. They‚Äôre very bothersome and cause sensitivity when anyone makes remarks about them, so I thought this would be great to see if it really does help reduce the appearance of stretch marks. What I‚Äôve done is taken pictures of the offending marks ‚Äúbefore‚Äù using this cream, and will be taking pictures in 30 to 60 days of ‚Äúafter‚Äù to see if I can tell a difference.

I will come back on here sometime between 30 to 60 days and post the progress that is seen with the use of this product. Now, so far, I like the ingredients listed. I like the whipped consistency that the treatment cream has, and the smell, although unusual, is a thumbs up because it‚Äôs almost a neutral odor, that‚Äôs good in that you can wear it and it doesn‚Äôt clash with any other scent you may have on.

As I put some of it on one of my stretch marks, I noticed that it filled in the thin lines of the stretched skin, and that there was no oiliness or stickiness to it. It kind of soaks into the stretch mark and stays where it‚Äôs put. I will update this review information over the next few months when I can see how well this treatment does in its claims to healing existing stretch marks and preventing future ones.

Disclosure: I bought this product with a promotional discount (or was given the product for free) in exchange for my honest and unbiased review. And, hey, I look at reviews before I buy something too, to make sure it‚Äôs a product that would serve my family in some positive way. I love to share my insight and opinion about the things I buy and I do so with Benjamin Franklin‚Äôs quote always in mind: Honesty is the best policy.

text:
Many years ago I found a vitamin E gel at the dollar store. Of course, that meant it wasn't going to be there forever because it was discontinued merchandise. I stocked up on it and it helped soothe the dried-out patches of skin that were home to plaque psoriasis. Once I ran out, I found a vitamin E cream which was an acceptable substitute aside from taking much longer to soak into my skin.

Recently I discovered this product. I have already used this manufacturer's aloe vera gel for decades so I tried it. It's soothing but the aloe in it can sting briefly. (I'm used to that from using pure aloe gel, so it doesn't bother me very much.)

This is a good price for three bottles of this size. I especially appreciate that they were shrink-wrapped together which prevented the caps from coming open in transit.

title: JUNK WORST THAN CHINESE
text:
Update: Eufy updated the app so users can connect multiple accounts to the scale. Some of the UX in the app is still clunky but it's tolerable. There is a menu with a lot of options/settings accessed by tapping your small profile picture and there is no indication that even a useful button that can be pressed. I take all the information besides the weight with a grain of salt. The amount of information gleaned from the bottom of your feet seems too good to be true and I have no way to verify it's accuracy.

The scale seems to work but can only connect with one account which wouldn't be a problem if more than one person with a phone wants to use it. The user interface in the app is terrible. You're supposed to be able to add multiple users to the only account that the scale can connect to but if there is a way to do it 2 people working together couldn't figure it out. Overall a very disappointing and frustrating experience. Luckily I haven't thrown away the packaging because I'm seriously considering returning the product. I'm giving it 2 stars because at least it worked for one person.

I figured out how to add users. Still 2 stars.

text: Excellent product. I searched all over for a liquid B12 without nasty additives and in an appropriate dose for a toddler to no avail. Anyway, for dosing, I've improvised with this product and my toddler loves it. She gets a single drop 2-3x/week which is still more than she needs, but not a super mega dose that everything else had.
